

\begin{frame}\frametitle{Computer simulations in the humanities?}
In literary studies, simulations are being used to help understand
\begin{itemize}
\item structural patterns of narratives in 19th C. novels (Sack)
\item how literary genres evolve over time (Sack)
\item 18th, 19th C. publishing networks (Throne)
\end{itemize}
\end{frame}

\begin{frame}\frametitle{Computer simulations in the humanities?}
Historians use simulations to understand historical events:
\begin{itemize}
\item (Naval) Battle of Trafalgar (Trautteur and Virgilio)
\item Conflicts between Ancient Roman factions (Graham)
\item Medieval military logistics (Murgatroyd et al.)
\item Why the Anasazi people disappeared from the American
Southwest mid-14th C. (Dean et. al, Axtell et al., Janssen)
\end{itemize}
\end{frame}

