\begin{frame}\frametitle{Computer simulations in the humanities?}
Philosophers use simulations for a variety of topics:
\begin{itemize}
\item How scientific theories change over time (Thagard, de
Langhe, Alexander)
\item How vague concepts arise (O'Connor)
\item The development of morals (Smead, Alexander, Skyrms, )
\item The development of linguistic conventions (Skyrms, Poproski)
\item How consensus and disagreement arises (Zolman, Grim et al., etc.)
\end{itemize}
\end{frame}
